This readme shows an example deployment on a Mac OS X system (tested in Macbook with Mac OS X 10.5.8):

 1. allow cgi-bin in your ~/Sites
   a. make sure cgi is enabled in /etc/apache2/httpd.conf
      Search for cgi in the file. make sure the following line is uncommented:

        AddHandler cgi-script .cgi


   b. create a directory ~/Sites/cgi-bin

   c. create a file <username>.conf under /etc/apache2/users. there might be one already there. just make sure sth similar to following is presented:

<Directory /Users/XXXXXX/Sites/cgi-bin>
    AllowOverride FileInfo AuthConfig Limit
    Options MultiViews Indexes SymLinksIfOwnerMatch Includes ExecCGI
    DirectoryIndex index.html index.cgi
    <Limit GET POST OPTIONS PROPFIND>
        Order allow,deny
        Allow from all
    </Limit>
    <LimitExcept GET POST OPTIONS PROPFIND>
        Order deny,allow
        Deny from all
    </LimitExcept>
</Directory>

      where XXXXXX is your usename  

 2. create a dedicated cgi-bin directory for jazzclub
  
  $ cd ~/Sites/cgi-bin
  $ mkdir jazzclub

 3. create a cgi script. here is an example

#!/usr/bin/env bash
source /path/to/luban/software/bin/envs.sh
cd /path/to/luban/software/jazzclub/cgi-bin
webmain.py $@ --web-weaver.controller-url=http://localhost/~linjiao/cgi-bin/jazzclub/main.cgi --web-weaver.html-base=http://localhost/~linjiao/jazzclub/ --web-weaver.cookie-path=/~linjiao/cgi-bin/jazzclub/ --web-weaver.use-cookie=1

  4. make a symbolic link on html dir tree

  $ cd ~/Sites
  $ ln -s /path/to/luban/software/jazzclub/html jazzclub

  5. make sure files are readable/writable for apache:

  use chown to change the ownership of following files to apache2

  /path/to/luban/software/jazzclub:
    log/*
    db.pickles/*
